{[show S]

Partner's 3\S is a limit raise, 11-12 points and good \S support. Decide what you would say next, then click on <b>BID</b> above. [BID 4\C]



What you DO NOT say next is 4NT. If partner answered 1 Key-Card you would not know what to do. If he has a red Ace you can make slam, but if his one Key-Card were the \CA you couldn't. Instead you make a control-showing bid of 4\C, promising first round control. Partner obliges you by bidding 4\H. What is your next bid? [BID 6\S]

[show NS]



Partner's bidding is like the Sherlock Holmes tale <u>Silver Blaze</u>, about the dog that didn't bark. Partner's \H bid shows that he <b>DOES</b> have the \HA, but equally important it shows that he <b>DOES NOT</b> have the \DA. So you know you don't have a \H loser but do have a \D loser. You bid 6\S.}


